summary:
25 Days Of Christmas: Day 11: Ivy saw mummy kissing Santa Claus. fluff - kids - words 700

This happens straight after Day 10...
caption:
25 Days Of Christmas:

Day 11: Ivy saw mummy kissing Santa Claus.

fluff - kids - words 700 This happens straight after Day 10

-.-.-

“That wasn’t kissing,” You said, hands running over your face stressfully. “That was mummy a second away from ‘sitting on Santa’s lap’.”

Breathing in deeply you fell down onto the closest couch, thinking of the best way to approach the subject with your little girl. Maybe a soft kiss on his cheek you could explain to her, but what she caught you in the middle of you wouldn’t know how to explain even if Harry wasn’t dressed as Santa.

“Come on, YN,” Harry came over to sit in front of you, hands sliding over your legs gently. “Just go up and talk with her. She’s two, who knows what she thinks she saw. One thing she did see though, was Santa and that was because of her mummy. Not just mummy and daddy putting the presents down, that would heave really ruined it for her.”

A small smile pulled at your lips and you pushed up to your feet, hands cupping either side of Harry’s face. “I’ll figure it out.” Pressing a quick kiss to the bed you drew back away from him. “I will meet you back in bed.”

Pushing open the door to Ivy’s room, you saw her rearranging all her reindeer toys, all eight of them so she could drive her bed like a sleigh. She looked up at you from beneath her sheets, a small frown on her face but not one tear in sight. That was a good thing at least.

“Hey, baby girl, why are you awake?” You ask, walking in to sit beside her on her bed, lifting whatever reindeer out of the way.

“I wanted to see Santa.” She pouts further.

Exhaling you reached over to place a hand on her tummy, giving it a squeeze. “Santa only comes when you’re asleep Ivy.”

“You saw him.” She argues, pout not budging from her face.

“Can mummy tell you a secret?” You ask her, hand giving another squeeze of her belly. Shaking her head, she tucked herself under her blankets. “A secret just for me and you. Daddy, Fee and Eli don’t need to know.”

Moving her eye’s, she looks up at you and you know she’s taken the bait. “Santa set mummy a letter. He had too many toys and needed mummy to help put them under the tree.”

“Mummy an elf?” she asked quietly, hand reaching down so she could thread her fingers with yours.

“Not an elf baby, they’re all at the workshop making presents. You can’t tell anybody though, it’s our secret. If you tell anybody, then Santa can’t come back.” You changed the tone of voice to a sound of slight horror and her mouth dropped a bit at the worry of Santa not coming back.

“I not tell.” She said shaking her head quickly, brown curls falling over her forehead. “Mummy and I secret.” Lifting her hand, she put a finger over her lips, shushing quietly.

Lifting your own finger, you put it over your lips as well, giving her a wink. “Our secret. Good night gorgeous. No sneaking downstairs though, it’s bedtime.”

“Okay mummy,” she replied pushing up so she could wrap her arms around you and pressing a kiss to your cheek. “Love you.”

“Love you to,” Kissing her cheek back you tucked her under the sheets, moving all her reindeers around her so she was surrounded by them. Giving her another kiss, you watched as her eyes fell closed, quickly falling asleep.

Giving her one last smile you left the room shutting the door carefully behind you. Your footsteps are quiet as you make your way back to your bedroom, checking on Fee and Eli as you passed their bedrooms.

A scoff left your mouth as you shut the door to your bedroom and you saw Harry on the bed, only in the red Santa pants and the beard. Heat covered your cheeks as you looked at him smirking at you.

“Christmas came early to mummy.” Running across the room, you jumped onto the bed, half tackling Harry to the mattress.

“Shh,” he chuckled hand looping around the back of your neck. “Santa isn’t supposed to wake the kids.”
